HEADWORD: Diabolify
<hw>Di`a*bol"i*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>diabolus</ets> devil + <ets>-fy</ets>.]</ety> <def>To ascribed
diabolical qualities to; to change into, or to represent as, a
devil.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Farindon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

